TITLE: Inlining Resolver Options in Awilix
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use inline resolver options in Awilix, including setting lifetime, injection mode, and custom naming for auto-loaded modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jeffijoe/awilix/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { RESOLVER, Lifetime, InjectionMode } from 'awilix'

export default class AwesomeService {
  constructor(awesomeRepository) {
    this.awesomeRepository = awesomeRepository
  }
}

AwesomeService[RESOLVER] = {
  name: 'superService',
  lifetime: Lifetime.SCOPED,
  injectionMode: InjectionMode.CLASSIC
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Implementing Per-Module Local Injections in Awilix
DESCRIPTION: Shows various ways to set up per-module local injections in Awilix, allowing for module-specific configuration values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jeffijoe/awilix/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { createContainer, Lifetime, asFunction } from 'awilix'
import createUserRepository from './repositories/userRepository'

const container = createContainer()
  .register({
    userRepository: asFunction(createUserRepository)
      .inject(() => ({ timeout: 2000 })),
  })
  .register({
    userRepository: asFunction(createUserRepository, {
      injector: () => ({ timeout: 2000 }),
    }),
  })
  .register(
    'userRepository',
    asFunction(createUserRepository, {
      injector: () => ({ timeout: 2000 }),
    }),
  )
  .loadModules([['repositories/*.js', { injector: () => ({ timeout: 2000 }) }]])
```

