TITLE: Implementing Scoped Logger Example in Awilix v4
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating the corrected scoped caching behavior in Awilix v4, showing how a Logger class with different prefixes is handled in root and scoped containers. This illustrates how scoped registrations now maintain their own cache rather than using parent container's cache.
SOURCE: https://github.com/jeffijoe/awilix/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// logger.js
export class Logger {
  constructor(loggerPrefix = 'root') {
    this.prefix = loggerPrefix
  }

  log(message) {
    console.log(`[${this.prefix}]: ${message}`)
  }
}
```

